<li><i>Literary Hub</i> published an excerpt from Nicolas Chevassus-au-Louis&rsquo;s <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674979451">Fraud in the Lab</a>, on the <a class="external" href="https://lithub.com/the-theranos-effect-when-cutting-edge-scientists-are-frauds/">&ldquo;Theranos effect&rdquo;&mdash;when spectacular discoveries turn out to be too good to be true</a>.</li>

<li>Brian Rosenwald, author of <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674185012">Talk Radio&rsquo;s America</a>, spoke with WAMU&rsquo;s <i>1A</i> about the <a class="external" href="https://the1a.org/shows/2019-08-12/conservative-talk-radio">radio roots that shaped today&rsquo;s GOP</a>.</li>

<li><i>Jezebel</i> interviewed Emily Remus about <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674987272">A Shoppers&rsquo; Paradise</a> and the <a class="external" href="https://pictorial.jezebel.com/when-did-america-decide-that-women-do-in-fact-be-shop-1836886713">early-twentieth-century origins of the &ldquo;women like shopping&rdquo; stereotype</a>.</li>

<li>A CNN.com report on <a class="external" href="https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/08/us/texas-matanza-descendants-el-paso-shooting/">past border violence victims&rsquo; descendants&rsquo; reactions to the El Paso shooting</a> featured analysis from <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674976436">The Injustice Never Leaves You</a> author Monica Mu&ntilde;oz Martinez.</li>

<li>On Utah Public Radio&rsquo;s <i>UnDisciplined</i>, <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674983700">Bored, Lonely, Angry, Stupid</a> coauthors Luke Fernandez and Susan Matt considered <a class="external" href="https://www.upr.org/post/undisciplined-climatologist-political-scientist-and-cultural-historian">which human emotions have been changed the most by recent developments in technology</a> [at 09:50].</li>

<li>Tony Jack, author of <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674976894">The Privileged Poor</a>, spoke with the <i>Boston Globe</i> about the <a class="external" href="https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2019/08/09/cash-strapped-students-are-skipping-meals-colleges/u0nP8iPbAEbbt2NrhrLlwI/story.html">increasingly recognized phenomenon of financially disadvantaged college students skipping meals</a>.</li>

<li>The <i>Wall Street Journal</i> spoke with <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674737853">Gropius</a> author Fiona MaCarthy on the occasion of the <a class="external" href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/designing-the-modern-world-11565378649">opening of the new Bauhaus Museum in Dessau, Germany</a>.</li>

<li>At <i>The Brains Blog</i>, <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674979581">Why Free Will Is Real</a> author Christian List made the <a class="external" href="http://philosophyofbrains.com/2019/08/12/1-the-naturalistic-case-for-free-will-the-challenge.aspx">naturalistic case for free will</a>.</li>

<li>An <a class="external" href="https://churchlifejournal.nd.edu/articles/the-dangerous-alliances-between-catholicism-and-phenomenology/">excerpt</a> from Edward Baring&rsquo;s <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674988378">Converts to the Real: Catholicism and the Making of Continental Philosophy</a> was published in <i>Church Life Journal</i>.</li>

<li>On the <i>Guardian</i> technology podcast <i>Chips with Everything</i>, <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674976696">The End of Forgetting</a> author Kate Eichhorn described the <a class="external" href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/audio/2019/aug/05/the-end-of-forgetting-chips-with-everything-podcast">dangers facing young people who may find it difficult to distance themselves from their pasts</a>&mdash;even long into the future.</li>

<li>Ganesh Sitaraman and Anne Alstott discussed <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674987333">The Public Option</a> with <a class="external publicationTitle" href="https://prospect.org/article/power-public-option-qa-ganesh-sitaraman-and-anne-alstott">The American Prospect</a> and <a class="external" href="https://www.wgbh.org/news/lifestyle/2019/08/05/a-public-option-for-everything">WGBH (Boston, MA)&rsquo;s Jim Braude and Margery Eagan</a>.</li>

<li><a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674237698">Bring the War Home</a> author Kathleen Belew <a class="external" href="https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/why-domestic-terrorism-is-an-underestimated-national-threat">explained the ideology behind the El Paso shooting</a> on <i>PBS NewsHour</i>.</li>

<li>Monica Mu&ntilde;oz Martinez, author of <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674976436">The Injustice Never Leaves You</a>, analyzed El Paso in the context of past anti-Mexican and anti-Chicano violence on <a class="external" href="https://www.msnbc.com/the-beat-with-ari/watch/hate-crime-expert-crimes-spike-around-trump-s-election-and-rhetoric-65442373554">MSNBC&rsquo;s <i>The Beat</i></a> and <a class="external" href="https://www.wbur.org/onpoint/2019/08/06/race-based-terrorism-in-wake-of-the-weekend-mass-shootings">WBUR (Boston, MA)&rsquo;s <i>On Point</i></a>.</li>

<li>Elizabeth Foster, author of <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674987661">African Catholic</a>, discussed with the <i>Washington Post</i> blog <i>Monkey Cage</i> <a class="external" href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/08/09/how-did-catholic-church-respond-africas-decolonization-this-new-book-explains/">how the Catholic Church responded to the decolonization of the continent</a>.</li>

<li><i>The Bloggers Karamazov</i> <a class="external" href="https://bloggerskaramazov.com/2019/08/06/a-chat-with-jonathan-paine-about-selling-the-story/">interviewed</a> Jonathan Paine about <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674988439">Selling the Story: Transaction and Narrative Value in Balzac, Dostoevsky, and Zola</a>.</li>

<li>In the <i>New York Times</i>, <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674237698">Bring the War Home</a> author Kathleen Belew placed the recent mass shooting in El Paso, TX, squarely within the <a class="external" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/04/opinion/el-paso-terrorism.html">rising spate of terrorist acts resulting from white nationalism</a>.</li>

<li>On WNYC&rsquo;s <i>The Takeaway</i>, Monica Mu&ntilde;oz Martinez, author of <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674976436">The Injustice Never Leaves You</a>, responded to the El Paso shooting in the context of <a class="external" href="https://www.wnycstudios.org/story/history-anti-latino-violence-us">America&rsquo;s dark&mdash;and under-recognized&mdash;history of anti-Mexican violence</a>.</li>

<li>Harvard University Press mourns the recent passing of <a class="external" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/06/books/toni-morrison-dead.html">Toni Morrison</a>, author of <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674976450">The Origin of Others</a> and <a class="publicationTitle" href="/catalog.php?isbn=9780674673779">Playing in the Dark: Whiteness and the Literary Imagination</a> among other critically acclaimed works of fiction and nonfiction; and of educator <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/01/education/vivian-paley-dead.html">Vivian Gussin Paley</a>, whose <a href="/results-list.php?author=1279">work in early childhood development</a> informed and elevated a generation of classroom teaching.</li>

*** End older items *** -->
		</ul><!-- End .recentNewsList -->
		<!-- End /includes/recentNews.php -->
