						<div id="blogExcerpt">
			<h4>From Our Blog</h4>
						<a class="blogImgLnk" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20200928094657/https://harvardpress.typepad.com/hup_publicity/2020/09/book-club-spotlight-the-privileged-poor.html"><img id="blogimage" alt="Jacket: The Privileged Poor: How Elite Colleges Are Failing Disadvantaged Students, by Anthony Abraham Jack, from Harvard University Press" class="asset asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341d17e553ef026be40e2c48200d img-responsive" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20200928094657im_/https://harvardpress.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341d17e553ef026be40e2c48200d-320wi" title="The Privileged Poor: How Elite Colleges Are Failing Disadvantaged Students, by Anthony Abraham Jack, from Harvard University Press"/></a>
						<p class="blogTitle"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20200928094657/https://harvardpress.typepad.com/hup_publicity/2020/09/book-club-spotlight-the-privileged-poor.html"><!-- September 10: -->Book Club Spotlight: The Privileged Poor</a></p>
			<p class="blogBlurb"> 			 				<em>As students around the world deliberate their options for further education, only made more challenging in a pandemic, we&rsquo;re reminded that getting in is only half the battle. In </em>The Privileged Poor: How Elite Colleges Are Failing Disadvantaged Students<em>, Anthony Abraham Jack asks how&mdash;and why&mdash;do disadvantaged students struggle at elite colleges? What can schools can do differently if these students are to thrive? As back to school season begins, we spoke to two university book clubs that read and discussed </em>The Privileged Poor<em> this summer.</e<><a class="readMore" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20200928094657/https://harvardpress.typepad.com/hup_publicity/2020/09/book-club-spotlight-the-privileged-poor.html">&hellip;</a></p>
		</div>
		
